article.headline: Jacksonville 87, South Carolina State 74
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Freshmen Lehmon Colbert and Corey Claitt each scored season highs of 17 points to lead Jacksonville to an 87-74 win over South Carolina State on Saturday. Colbert scored 12 of his points after the intermission to power the Dolphins second half surge in which they outscored the visitors 52-38, the most points scored in a half by JU in coach Cliff Warren's two years with the Dolphins. Evan Jefferson hit back-to-back 3-point shots at the 14:34 mark of the second half to start an 18-4 Jacksonville surge. The outburst gave the Dolphins (3-2) a 10-point lead at 59-49 with just under 11 minutes left. Colbert hit successive baskets at the 4:28 mark to finish another 10-2 surge, giving JU a 16-point lead at 77-61, its largest margin of the game. Jacksonville, which has struggled at the free throw line this year, hit a season high 88 percent by converting 37-of-42 shots from the foul line. The Dolphins had six players in double figures, including four of its five starters along with Evan Jefferson and Tyrone Curnell who had 10 or more points coming off the bench for a second consecutive game. Jason Flagler, who scored 15 points, was one of three players in double figures for the Bulldogs.
